Okay.

00:03:47.379 --> 00:03:49.379
The sister isn't a bad person.

00:03:49.379 --> 00:03:54.379
But we can ask, what's she teaching her daughter about the wife's role in the family?

00:03:54.379 --> 00:03:58.379
And what's her son learning about taking the lead as the man of the house?

00:03:58.379 --> 00:04:02.379
He hasn't had a man in his life for a long time.

00:04:02.379 --> 00:04:04.379
No, there is one.

00:04:04.379 --> 00:04:09.379
It's safe to say that the kids will stand a better chance of having a successful marriage themselves

00:04:09.379 --> 00:04:13.379
when they see their parents pulling together.

00:04:13.379 --> 00:04:17.379
A little later, we'll see how the husband handles the situation.

00:04:17.379 --> 00:04:20.379
And we, brothers, are going to want to pay attention.

00:04:20.379 --> 00:04:24.819
This is a classic.

00:04:24.819 --> 00:04:30.819
Family life is more pleasant when dad, mom, and the kids work together as a team.

00:04:30.819 --> 00:04:32.819
The family head is the captain.

00:04:32.819 --> 00:04:37.819
He needs to make sure that everyone knows what goal is the family's working toward,

00:04:37.819 --> 00:04:41.819
and how each one can contribute toward achieving those goals.

00:04:41.819 --> 00:04:47.819
When it's your family's turn to help clean the kingdom hall, or a convention venue, for example,

00:04:47.819 --> 00:04:50.819
don't leave the kids at home. They're part of the team.

00:04:50.819 --> 00:04:53.819
Don't go there with half the team.

00:04:53.819 --> 00:04:57.819
Let them experience the joy that comes from serving others.

00:04:57.819 --> 00:04:59.819
Let them work along with you.

00:04:59.819 --> 00:05:03.819
If you're assigned to clean the restrooms, don't complain about it.

00:05:03.819 --> 00:05:05.819
A very fine example.

00:05:05.819 --> 00:05:09.819
Her children will learn that, when there's work to be done, we just do it.

00:05:09.819 --> 00:05:14.819
We aren't picky about what we will and will not do.

00:05:14.819 --> 00:05:18.819
And we don't feel that some jobs are beneath us.

00:05:18.819 --> 00:05:25.819
Now this is in line with Paul's counsel, found at Philippians chapter 2, verses 3 and 4.

00:05:25.819 --> 00:05:28.819
Let's look that up.

00:05:28.819 --> 00:05:30.819
Let's go to exercise.

00:05:30.819 --> 00:05:37.819
Philippians chapter 2, verses 3 and 4.

00:05:37.819 --> 00:05:40.819
Now we're thinking about the family as a team here.

00:05:40.819 --> 00:05:51.819
It says, do nothing out of contentiousness, or out of egotism, but with humility, consider others superior to you,

00:05:51.819 --> 00:05:59.819
as you will look out not only for your own interests, but also for the interests of others.

00:05:59.819 --> 00:06:02.819
When there's work to be done, someone has to do it.

00:06:02.819 --> 00:06:08.819
Do I think that I'm so special that someone else has to look after it?

00:06:08.819 --> 00:06:12.819
Some families volunteer to help with kingdom hall maintenance.

00:06:12.819 --> 00:06:16.819
When the kids are old enough, they can work on other projects like working on an assembly hall.

00:06:16.819 --> 00:06:18.819
They have a ball.

00:06:18.819 --> 00:06:23.819
The friendships that you and your young people will forge can last a lifetime.

00:06:23.819 --> 00:06:25.819
And here's a bonus.

00:06:25.819 --> 00:06:34.819
When the young people go to a circuit assembly or a regional convention, they'll have good friends to associate with, both young and old.

00:06:34.819 --> 00:06:36.819
People they've been working with.

00:06:36.819 --> 00:06:42.420
What about working around the house?

00:06:42.420 --> 00:06:48.420
Some parents feel that the children shouldn't have to help out at all because they have their schoolwork to do.

00:06:48.420 --> 00:06:51.420
But their schoolwork is something they do for themselves.

00:06:51.420 --> 00:06:55.420
How are they contributing to the welfare of the family?

00:06:55.420 --> 00:06:59.420
How are they learning to serve others unselfishly?

00:06:59.420 --> 00:07:06.420
It's good for a child to feel that he has an important role in the household and that people are counting on him.

00:07:06.420 --> 00:07:10.420
Think what that does for his self-respect.

00:07:10.420 --> 00:07:12.420
A father named Stephen said,

00:07:12.420 --> 00:07:17.420
When nothing is expected of them, children learn that they're here to be served.

00:07:17.420 --> 00:07:24.420
And they grow up with a distorted view of what life will require of them.

00:07:24.420 --> 00:07:30.420
We might ask, will a young person with that attitude even be able to keep a job?

00:07:30.420 --> 00:07:36.420
When some of the world lose their job, they remain unemployed for a long time.

00:07:36.420 --> 00:07:38.420
They can't pay the bills.

00:07:38.420 --> 00:07:41.420
Yet there are job opportunities all around them.

00:07:41.420 --> 00:07:44.420
But they consider those jobs beneath them.

00:07:44.420 --> 00:07:49.420
And what's one of the most annoying traits an employee can have?

00:07:49.420 --> 00:07:51.420
Ask any boss.

00:07:51.420 --> 00:07:54.420
When the worker is asked to do something, he replies,

00:07:54.420 --> 00:07:56.420
that's not my job.

00:07:57.420 --> 00:08:02.420
Teach your child that anything that needs to be done is his job

00:08:02.420 --> 00:08:05.420
if he's old enough and capable of doing it.

00:08:05.420 --> 00:08:10.670
How early should parents start to assign chores to their children?

00:08:10.670 --> 00:08:15.670
Some experts have found that children who are three years old

00:08:15.670 --> 00:08:19.670
or even younger can be taught to help out.

00:08:19.670 --> 00:08:24.670
They can learn to pick up their toys, clean up spills, sort laundry.

00:08:24.670 --> 00:08:29.670
Older children can vacuum, wash the car, prepare a meal.

00:08:29.670 --> 00:08:34.669
I'm happy to say that many young brothers here at Bethel are excellent cooks,

00:08:34.669 --> 00:08:39.669
which is often the result of fine parental training.

